t descendant, reflect on Garrison as a political activist, an internationalist, an advocate of feminism, and more. Together they present a new appraisal of one of America's most challenging, inspiring, and controversial historical figures.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aAbolitionistsxBiographyxUnited States. 0aAbolitionistszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aAntislavery movementsxHistoryx19th centuryxUnited StatesxUnited States. 0aAntislavery movementszUnited StatesxHistoryy19th century. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Political.2bisacsh1 aStewart, James Brewer, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300152401423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300152401.jpg  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles